
[1]weasel

   WEASEL, WEESEL, n. s as z. A small animal of the genus Mustela, which
   lives under the roots of trees, or in other holes, and feeds on small
   birds, but particularly on mice. A weasel that frequents barns and
   corn-houses, frees them from rats and mice, and is sometimes deemed a
   very useful inmate.
